Class Server

java.lang.Object
  edu.uw.cs.cse461.sp12.timingframing.Server

public class Server
extends java.lang.Object

A server accepts connections from Clients, and then paces output to them. The Server terminates only when the Client breaks the connection.

Constructor Detail

Server

public Server()
       throws java.io.IOException
Constructs, but does not start, a Server.

The baseline server supports a fixed set of inter-symbol times, given by array Properties.SERVER_INTERSYMBOL_TIME_VEC. Each inter-symbol time is associated with a server port to which clients can connect. A thread is associated with each server port, because the thread blocks waiting for connections.

To avoid the risk of running out of open file handles, we read the data file into a String when the server is created. When clients connect, it is served from that String.

Throws:
java.io.IOException
